<div id="post-1159228" class="blog-post position-6 even-post"><div class="even-post-inner blog-post-inner"><h1 class="title"><a href="http://softwarelivre.org/libreoffice/blog/libreoffice-conference-2013-proposals">LibreOffice Conference 2013 Proposals</a></h1><span class="publishing-info"><span class="date">17 de Dezembro de 2012, 0:00</span><span class="author">, por Software Livre Brasil</span><span class="comments"> - <a href="/libreoffice/blog/libreoffice-conference-2013-proposals#comments_list"><span class='comment-count hide'>0</span><span class='comment-count-write-out'>sem comentários ainda</span></a></span></span><p>Following our public <a href="http://wiki.documentfoundation.org/Marketing/CallforLocation">call for locations</a>, The Document Foundation has received the following two proposals for hosting the LibreOffice Conference 2013, in alphabetical order:</p>
<ul>
<li>Milan, Italy<br>
<em>Read the <a href="http://documentfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2012/12/milan2013.pdf">original proposal in PDF format</a> here.</em>
</li>
<li>Montreal, Canada<br>
<em>Read the <a href="http://documentfoundation.files.wordpress.com/2012/12/montreal2013.pdf">original proposal in PDF format</a> here.</em>
</li>
</ul>
<p>The Document Foundation would like to thank all proponents for their support, which is truly appreciated! Soon, we will start a public vote to determine the location of the 2013 Conference. In the meantime, we invite the community to discuss with the proponents <a href="http://www.mail-archive.com/discuss@documentfoundation.org/info.html">on our discuss mailing list</a> any questions they have.</p>
<p>Thanks again, and looking forward to seeing you in 2013!</p>
