<div id="post-1109753" class="blog-post position-13 odd-post"><div class="odd-post-inner blog-post-inner"><h1 class="title"><a href="http://softwarelivre.org/libreoffice/blog/the-libreoffice-community-organises-a-6-day-test-marathon-to-help-preparing-the-new-4.0-version-of-libreoffice">The LibreOffice community organises a 6 day Test Marathon to help preparing the new 4.0 version of LibreOffice</a></h1><span class="publishing-info"><span class="date">8 de Dezembro de 2012, 0:00</span><span class="author">, por Software Livre Brasil</span><span class="comments"> - <a href="/libreoffice/blog/the-libreoffice-community-organises-a-6-day-test-marathon-to-help-preparing-the-new-4.0-version-of-libreoffice#comments_list"><span class='comment-count hide'>0</span><span class='comment-count-write-out'>sem comentários ainda</span></a></span></span><p>Berlin, December 7 2012,  The Document Foundation announces the LibreOffice 4.0 Test Marathon. During 6 days, from December 14 to 19, users and supporters around the world will be testing the first beta of the upcoming LibreOffice 4.0.</p>
